This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of sequence-to-sequence models for language generation, which is a core topic in the field of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel probabilistic loss and a training and inference procedure, which are relevant to machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of pre-trained word embeddings, which are commonly used in NLP and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed models on the task of neural machine translation, which involves processing and generating images. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
